-- Foreigners Invested $1.2 Billion in Iran This Year: TV
-- B y   Y e g a n e h   S a l e h i
-- 2012-09-03T09:25:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-03/foreigners-invested-1-2-billion-in-iran-this-year-tv.html
Iran  has gotten $1.2 billion in
foreign direct investment since the current Iranian year began
on March 20, the state TV news website reported, citing Deputy
Economy Minister Behrouz Alishiri.  As much as 55 percent of the money was invested in oil and
gas projects and 30 percent in industry, Alishiri said,
according to state TV.  Foreign direct investment in the Persian Gulf country
amounted to $4.3 billion last year, he said, according to the
 report .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yeganeh Salehi in Tehran at 
